<subSubSection lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
The first volume of the Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
1844-1862) was published in parts. Plate 19, with a figure of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Clausiliidae" genus="Montenegrina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Montenegrina helvola" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="helvola">Montenegrina helvola</taxonomicName>
but without description, was printed in 1853. The description (at p. 176), however, was published only in 1860 (
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes, FW" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="157 - 203" title="Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet von Martini und Chemnitz (1837 - 1920), bibliography of the volumes in Goettingen." url="10.3366/anh.1999.26.2.157" volume="26" year="1999">Welter-Schultes 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Without specific type locality it was not possible to ascertain where 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Küster’s">Kuester's</normalizedToken>
material originated from. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilch, A" editor="Wenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Borntraeger, Berlin" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="376 - 834" title="Euthyneura." volumeTitle="Gastropoda, Handbuch der Palaeozoologie" year="1960">Zilch (1960)</bibRefCitation>
depicted a specimen from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Krujë">Kruje</normalizedToken>
, which was subsequently used as reference for the taxon without any nomenclatural relevance. The original type material could not be found in the public collections that currently hold 
<pageBreakToken pageId="32" pageNumber="33" start="start">remnants</pageBreakToken>
of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Küster’s">Kuester's</normalizedToken>
collection. Therefore, we can reasonably assume that it has been lost. In order to clarify and fix the taxonomic status and the type locality of 
<taxonomicName lsidName="helvola" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="helvola">helvola</taxonomicName>
it is necessary to designate a neotype, in accordance with ICZN Art. 75.3. To preserve nomenclatural stability, we think it is justified to designate as neotype the specimen that has been used as reference for the taxon since 
<bibRefCitation author="Zilch, A" editor="Wenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Borntraeger, Berlin" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" pagination="376 - 834" title="Euthyneura." volumeTitle="Gastropoda, Handbuch der Palaeozoologie" year="1960">Zilch (1960)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, A" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici Musei Polonici Historiae Naturalis" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="99 - 126" title="Systematisches Verzeichnis der mir heute bekannten Arten und Formen der Clausiliiden. III." volume="3" year="1924">Wagner (1924)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName lsidName="helvola" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="helvola">helvola</taxonomicName>
as a species of 
<taxonomicName authority="A.J.Wagner, 1924" authorityName="A.J.Wagner" authorityYear="1924" class="Gastropoda" family="Clausiliidae" genus="Alpidelima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alpidelima" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Alpidelima</taxonomicName>
. But in the same paper he listed it under 
<taxonomicName authority="A.J.Wagner, 1924" authorityName="A.J.Wagner" authorityYear="1924" class="Gastropoda" family="Clausiliidae" genus="Albanodelima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Albanodelima" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Albanodelima</taxonomicName>
, suggesting 
<taxonomicName authority="A.J.Wagner, 1924" authorityName="A.J.Wagner" authorityYear="1924" class="Gastropoda" family="Clausiliidae" genus="Alpidelima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Alpidelima" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Alpidelima</taxonomicName>
could have been merely a typographic error.
</paragraph>
